'''El Centro Integrado de Tecnología Apropiada (CITA)''' is a [[Cuba]]n [[appropriate technology]] organization. It is the equivalent of the UK's Centre for Alternative Technology.<ref>[http://www.cosg.supanet.com/cita.html CITA as Cuba's CAT-equivalent] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080618010737/http://www.cosg.supanet.com/cita.html |date=2008-06-18 }}</ref> It is stationed at [[Camagüey]] (Circunvalación Norte). 

In 2005 a representative of CITA participated in the "Public Seminar Series" of the [[International Institute for Resource Industries and Sustainability Studies]] (IRIS), on the topic ''Renewable Energy in Cuba: Sustainable Solutions for the Future (April, 2005)''. [http://webcache.googleusercontent.com/search?q=cache:3u5C98SzACoJ:www.haskayne.ucalgary.ca/research/centres/iris/research/centres/iris/media/seminarseries.pdf+%22Centre+for+Appropriate+Technology%22+canada+%22University+of+Waterloo%22+-%22It+has+adapted+tools+of+nearby+Mennonite%22&hl=en&gl=uk&ct=clnk&cd=1]{{dead link|date=December 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}

