{{Infobox company | name = Posiva | logo = | type = [[Osakeyhtiö|Oy]] | traded_as = | foundation = {{Start date|1995}} | location = [[Eurajoki]], [[Finland]] | key_people = | industry = [[Energy industry|Energy]] | products = [[High-level radioactive waste management|Nuclear waste management]] | revenue = | operating_income = | net_income = | assets = | equity = | num_employees = | owner = [[Teollisuuden Voima]] and [[Fortum]] | subsid = | homepage = {{URL|www.posiva.fi/en/}} }}
'''Posiva Oy''' is a Finnish company with headquarters in the municipality of [[Eurajoki]], [[Finland]]. It was founded in 1995 by [[Teollisuuden Voima]] (60% of stock) and [[Fortum]] (40% of stock),<ref>[http://www.posiva.fi/en/posiva Posiva's website]</ref> two Finnish nuclear plant operators, for researching and creating a method of final disposal of spent nuclear fuel from their plants.<ref> {{cite web | title = Nuclear waste tomb soon to reach final depth | date = 10 May 2010 | publisher = [[Helsingin Sanomat]] | url = http://www.hs.fi/english/article/Nuclear+waste+tomb+soon+to+reach+final+depth/1135256728600 | accessdate = 12 August 2012}} </ref><ref> {{cite news | title = Approval for expanded Olkiluoto repository | date = 4 June 2009 | publisher = [[World Nuclear Association#Public_information|World Nuclear News]] | url = http://www.world-nuclear-news.org/WR-Approval_for_expanded_Olkiluoto_repository-0406098.html | accessdate = 12 August 2012}} </ref><ref> {{cite web | title = Finnish nuclear waste may rest in peace | date = September 2011 | publisher = This Is Finland | url = http://finland.fi/Public/default.aspx?contentid=228885&nodeid=41799&culture=en-US | accessdate = 12 August 2012}} </ref>
For this purpose, Posiva is currently constructing the [[Onkalo spent nuclear fuel repository]], the world's first [[deep geological repository]], at the [[Olkiluoto Nuclear Power Plant]] site.
